#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.187897449072265,67,"Not so neither;" but if I had wit enough to get out of this wood
column2: I have enough to serve mine own turn.""
column3: With half that wish the wisher's eyes be pressed!"""

column1: #Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.191109936333476,92,"I had rather have a handful or two of dried peas.","Why, then, you left me - O, the gods forbid!";
#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.217445882718981,32,"I have a device to make all well.","Help me, Lysander, help me!";
#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.222817731471774,12,"Now name the rest of the players.","Belike for want of rain, which I could well Beteem them from the tempest of my eyes.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.223792654208777,47,"Some man or other must present Wall.","Then let us teach our trial patience Because it is a customary cross, As due to love as thoughts and dreams and sighs, Wishes and tears, poor fancy's followers.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.235230217817476,108,"I will tell you everything right as it fell out.","Either death or you I'll find immediately.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.236988297287969,37,"Let it be written in eight and eight.","Then let us teach our trial patience Because it is a customary cross, As due to love as thoughts and dreams and sighs, Wishes and tears, poor fancy's followers.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.244491386932942,27,"What beard were I best to play it in?","I would my father looked but with my eyes.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.248703719053514,53,"Why do they run away?","Methought a serpent ate my heart away, And you sat smiling at his cruel prey.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Bottom_MND",0.251933658845302,75,"Good Master Mustardseed, I know your patience well.","Do thy best To pluck this crawling serpent from my breast.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.253656760782938,65,"One lion may when many asses do.","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""
#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.25635745433744,53,"By day's approach look to be visited.","-  In earnest, shall I say?";
#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.260520768725571,62,"Do not you think The Duke was here and bid us follow him?","It cannot be but thou hast murdered him.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.261868966217692,59,"These things seem small and undistinguishable, Like far-off mountains turnèd into clouds.","The sun was not so true unto the day As he to me.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.269606758988685,20,"You spend your passion on a misprised mood.","I swoon almost with fear.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.271672448190015,58,"But, as in health, come to my natural taste, Now I do wish it, love it, long for it, And will forevermore be true to it.","Thy love ne'er alter till thy sweet life end!";
#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.298499363704801,57,"But like a sickness did I loathe this food.","We must starve our sight From lovers' food till morrow deep midnight.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.298797882334862,23,"There is no following her in this fierce vein.","His folly, Helena, is no fault of mine.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.307039344560879,41,"For I perceive A weak bond holds you.","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""
#Hermia_MND,"#Demetrius_MND",0.309204253572933,70,"He should have worn the horns on his head.","So should a murderer look, so dead, so grim.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.22617574724937,9,"But either it was different in blood -","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""
#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.25076861423501,38,"Things growing are not ripe until their season;" So I
column3: till now ripe not to reason.""
column4: We must starve our sight From lovers' food till morrow deep midnight."""

column1: #Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.260012164166534,6,"Why is your cheek so pale?","I would my father looked but with my eyes.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.271400739178346,53,"Why should he stay whom love doth press to go?","The more I hate, the more he follows me.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.287859502562487,46,"How can these things in me seem scorn to you, Bearing the badge of faith to prove them true?","Then let us teach our trial patience Because it is a customary cross, As due to love as thoughts and dreams and sighs, Wishes and tears, poor fancy's followers.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.293914798849278,7,"How chance the roses there do fade so fast?","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""

#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.302060281696487,52,"Helen, it is not so.","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""
#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.30377884733526,71,"Get you gone, you dwarf, You minimus of hind'ring knotgrass made, You bead, you acorn -","Thou art not by mine eye, Lysander, found;" Mine ear

#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.312207717288265,11,"Or else it stood upon the choice of friends -","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""
#Hermia_MND,"#Lysander_MND",0.313233054590771,68,"Therefore be out of hope, of question, of doubt.","Pray thou for us, And good luck grant thee thy Demetrius.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.211382227832398,95,"This sport, well carried, shall be chronicled.","Lysander and myself will fly this place.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.222558706659614,80,"Now I perceive they have conjoined all three To fashion this false sport in spite of me.","Tell true, even for my sake!";
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.243430030071741,43,"We should be wooed and were not made to woo.","Too high to be enthralled to low.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.252133639720846,70,"Nor none, in my mind, now you give her o'er.","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.262723787179127,26,"But yet you draw not iron, for my heart Is true as steel.","Take comfort: he no more shall see my face.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.263789625566489,67,"Will you give her o'er?","Ah, good Demetrius, wilt thou give him me?";
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.267283228395783,79,"Lo, she is one of this confederacy!","What a dream was here!";

#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.269591694576883,88,"Our sex, as well as I, may chide you for it, Though I alone do feel the injury.","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.273892181245747,78,"Never did mockers waste more idle breath.","An adder did it, for with doubler tongue Than thine, thou serpent, never adder stung.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.274247586205821,116,"I will not trust you, I, Nor longer stay in your curst company.","You, mistress, all this coil is long of you.";
#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.175953131477004,61,"Two of both kinds makes up four.","Nothing but "low" and "little"?";
#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.193016216346605,43,"That must needs be sport alone.","But, gentle friend, for love and courtesy, Lie further off in human modesty.";
#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.201021253520105,21,"I'll be an auditor -  An actor too perhaps, if I see cause.","Either death or you I'll find immediately.";
#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.203516290220926,36,"This is the woman, but not this the man.","O hell, to choose love by another's eyes!";

#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.219779797837055,23,"I'll lead you about a round, Through bog, through bush, through brake, through brier.","Find you out a bed, For I upon this bank will rest my head.";
#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.230544614945563,42,"Then will two at once woo one.","Henceforth be never numbered among men.";

#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.245332190130742,20,"What hempen homespuns have we swagg'ring here So near the cradle of the Fairy Queen?","Then let us teach our trial patience Because it is a customary cross, As due to love as thoughts and dreams and sighs, Wishes and tears, poor fancy's followers.";
#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.252658458062072,10,"I'll put a girdle round about the Earth In forty minutes.","Lysander and myself will fly this place.";
#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.25710979589907,63,"Cupid is a knavish lad Thus to make poor females mad.","What love could press Lysander from my side?";
#Hermia_MND,"#RobinGoodfellow_MND",0.26698108377405,28,"When I did him at this advantage take, An ass's noll I fixèd on his head.","Find you out a bed, For I upon this bank will rest my head.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.207983675363246,8,"How long within this wood intend you stay?","And in the wood where often you and I Upon faint primrose beds were wont to lie, Emptying our bosoms of their counsel sweet, There my Lysander and myself shall meet And thence from Athens turn away our eyes To seek new friends and stranger companies.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.257135836945193,95,"And the owner of it blest, Ever shall in safety rest.","So will I grow, so live, so die, my lord, Ere I will yield my virgin patent up Unto his Lordship whose unwishèd yoke My soul consents not to give sovereignty.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.26869478158735,43,"This falls out better than I could devise.","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius."""
#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.273776246141947,23,"I am invisible, And I will overhear their conference.","Take comfort: he no more shall see my face.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.274913265827507,41,"I wonder if Titania be awaked;" Then what it was that next came in her eye
column2: Which she must dote on in extremity.""
column3: Before the time I did Lysander see Seemed Athens as a paradise to me."""

column1: #Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.275564180057761,29,"And there the snake throws her enameled skin, Weed wide enough to wrap a fairy in.","So will I grow, so live, so die, my lord, Ere I will yield my virgin patent up Unto his Lordship whose unwishèd yoke My soul consents not to give sovereignty.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.275694075127828,52,"Flower of this purple dye, Hit with Cupid's archery, Sink in apple of his eye.","My good Lysander, I swear to thee by Cupid's strongest bow, By his best arrow with the golden head, By the simplicity of Venus' doves, By that which knitteth souls and prospers loves, And by that fire which burned the Carthage queen When the false Trojan under sail was seen, By all the vows that ever men have broke (In number more than ever women spoke), In that same place thou hast appointed me, Tomorrow truly will I meet with thee.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.2779107209848,68,"We may effect this business yet ere day.","We must starve our sight From lovers' food till morrow deep midnight.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.280151137110092,49,"All fancy-sick she is and pale of cheer With sighs of love that costs the fresh blood dear.","Such separation, as may well be said, Becomes a virtuous bachelor and a maid.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Oberon_MND",0.283362561929806,42,"What night-rule now about this haunted grove?","We must starve our sight From lovers' food till morrow deep midnight.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.188193998500859,54,"How came these things to pass?","Then let us teach our trial patience Because it is a customary cross, As due to love as thoughts and dreams and sighs, Wishes and tears, poor fancy's followers.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.218699155757652,8,"The fold stands empty in the drownèd field, And crows are fatted with the murrain flock.","And in the wood where often you and I Upon faint primrose beds were wont to lie, Emptying our bosoms of their counsel sweet, There my Lysander and myself shall meet And thence from Athens turn away our eyes To seek new friends and stranger companies.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.22854646326708,36,"-  Peaseblossom, Cobweb, Mote, and Mustardseed!","Help me, Lysander, help me!";

#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.251444534463314,12,"Therefore the moon, the governess of floods, Pale in her anger, washes all the air, That rheumatic diseases do abound.","Before the time I did Lysander see Seemed Athens as a paradise to me.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.257551860446285,32,"I am a spirit of no common rate.","Then I well perceive you are not nigh.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.265780751218148,14,"The spring, the summer, The childing autumn, angry winter, change Their wonted liveries, and the mazèd world By their increase now knows not which is which.","Belike for want of rain, which I could well Beteem them from the tempest of my eyes.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.272769227292589,9,"The nine-men's-morris is filled up with mud, And the quaint mazes in the wanton green, For lack of tread, are undistinguishable.","Belike for want of rain, which I could well Beteem them from the tempest of my eyes.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.273951612808339,40,"Tie up my lover's tongue.","Do thy best To pluck this crawling serpent from my breast.";
#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.279102631606907,1,"I have forsworn his bed and company.","I give him curses, yet he gives me love.";

#Hermia_MND,"#Titania_MND",0.279553092603454,7,"The ox hath therefore stretched his yoke in vain, The plowman lost his sweat, and the green corn Hath rotted ere his youth attained a beard.","Take comfort: he no more shall see my face.";
